<paragraph blockId="7.[136,1452,878,1229]" pageId="7" pageNumber="268">Stromata usually widely effused, dark brown, studded with small stellate ostiloles, surrounded by a black line within the substrate; perithecia monostichous or distichous, singly erumpent, 150–200 µm diam., with short ostiolar necks. Asci cylindrical, paraphysate, 35–40 × 5–7 µm in spore bearing part, stalks of different length (up to 60 µm long), containing 8 biseriate ascospores, apical ring non-amyloid. Ascospores one-celled, allantoid, yellowish, 7–9 × 1.7–1.9 µm.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="268" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="7.[136,1452,878,1229]" box="[189,1014,1022,1049]" pageId="7" pageNumber="268">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,318,1022,1048]" pageId="7" pageNumber="268">Etymology</emphasis>
:—Refers to the superficial similarity with 
<taxonomicName box="[801,1007,1022,1048]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Diatrypaceae" genus="Diatrype" kingdom="Fungi" order="Xylariales" pageId="7" pageNumber="268" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="undulata">
<emphasis box="[801,1007,1022,1048]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="268">Diatrype undulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[136,1452,878,1229]" pageId="7" pageNumber="268">
The similarity of stromata in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lar. N. Vassiljeva &amp; H. X. Ma" authorityYear="2014" box="[522,768,1058,1084]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Diatrypaceae" genus="Diatrype" kingdom="Fungi" order="Xylariales" pageId="7" pageNumber="268" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="subundulata">
<emphasis box="[522,768,1058,1084]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="268">Diatrype subundulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[825,960,1058,1084]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Diatrypaceae" genus="Diatrype" kingdom="Fungi" order="Xylariales" pageId="7" pageNumber="268" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="undulata">
<emphasis box="[825,960,1058,1084]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="268">D. undulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
could be seen at 
<figureCitation box="[1159,1337,1058,1084]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–13" captionStartId="6.[136,243,1575,1597]" captionTargetBox="[378,1209,190,1551]" captionTargetId="figure-21@6.[378,1209,190,1551]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 9–13. Stromata of Diatrype species: 9. D. hypoxyloides. 10. D. platystoma. 11. D. stigma. 12. D. subundulata. 13. D. undulata. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5153769" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5153769/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="268">Figs. 12 and 13</figureCitation>
, but these species differ in their ascospores. The specimens of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lar. N. Vassiljeva &amp; H. X. Ma" authorityYear="2014" box="[750,927,1094,1120]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Diatrypaceae" genus="Diatrype" kingdom="Fungi" order="Xylariales" pageId="7" pageNumber="268" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="subundulata">
<emphasis box="[750,927,1094,1120]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="268">D. subundulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the south-east of 
<collectingCountry box="[1207,1282,1094,1120]" name="Russia" pageId="7" pageNumber="268">Russia</collectingCountry>
were wrongly identified as 
<taxonomicName authority="Syd." authorityName="Syd." box="[287,559,1130,1156]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Diatrypaceae" genus="Diatrype" kingdom="Fungi" order="Xylariales" pageId="7" pageNumber="268" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="spilomea">
<emphasis box="[287,497,1130,1156]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="268">Diatrype spilomea</emphasis>
Syd.
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Vasilyeva, L. N." box="[576,757,1130,1156]" pageId="7" pageNumber="268" pagination="1 - 32" refId="ref5553" refString="Vasilyeva, L. N. (2011) Ascomycetes: Sordariomycetidae, Dothideomycetidae, Erysiphomycetidae, Rhytismomycetidae. In: Li, Y. &amp; Azbukina, Z. M. (Eds.) Fungi of Ussuri River Valley. Science Press, Beijing, 1 - 32." type="book chapter" year="2011">Vasilyeva 2011</bibRefCitation>
). The latter species has smaller ascospores comparable with those of 
<taxonomicName box="[233,367,1166,1192]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Diatrypaceae" genus="Diatrype" kingdom="Fungi" order="Xylariales" pageId="7" pageNumber="268" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="undulata">
<emphasis box="[233,367,1166,1192]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="268">D. undulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The new species 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lar. N. Vassiljeva &amp; H. X. Ma" authorityYear="2014" box="[572,744,1166,1192]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Diatrypaceae" genus="Diatrype" kingdom="Fungi" order="Xylariales" pageId="7" pageNumber="268" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="subundulata">
<emphasis box="[572,744,1166,1192]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="268">D. subundulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
seems to be restricted to 
<taxonomicName box="[1030,1136,1167,1193]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Sapindaceae" genus="Acer" kingdom="Plantae" order="Sapindales" pageId="7" pageNumber="268" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[1030,1083,1167,1193]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="268">Acer</emphasis>
spp.
</taxonomicName>
and the area around the Sea of 
<collectingCountry box="[166,230,1203,1229]" name="Japan" pageId="7" pageNumber="268">Japan</collectingCountry>
(north-eastern provinces of 
<collectingCountry box="[547,617,1202,1228]" name="China" pageId="7" pageNumber="268">China</collectingCountry>
, south of eastern 
<collectingCountry box="[813,893,1202,1229]" name="Russia" pageId="7" pageNumber="268">Russia</collectingCountry>
).
</paragraph>
